content:
Root fix: batch reaper into small chunks, commit each batch, add index on `expires_at`. Stops single long txn from holding locks/IO. Reaper still runs every 23min, just bounded chunks.

```sql
-- migration: index prevents full scan, keeps each batch fast
CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY IF NOT EXISTS idx_sessions_expires_at
  ON sessions (expires_at)
  WHERE expires_at IS NOT NULL;
```

```java
// scheduler/SessionReaper.java
@Scheduled(cron = "0 */23 * * * *")
public void reapExpiredSessions() {
    final int BATCH_SIZE   = 1000;
    final int MAX_BATCHES  = 500;           // safety cap: 500k/run
    final long PAUSE_MS    = 50;            // yield to checkout traffic

    long cutoff = System.currentTimeMillis();
    int totalDeleted = 0;

    for (int i = 0; i < MAX_BATCHES; i++) {
        int deleted = txTemplate.execute(status ->
            jdbc.update(
                "DELETE FROM sessions " +
                "WHERE id IN (" +
                "  SELECT id FROM sessions " +
                "  WHERE expires_at < ? " +
                "  ORDER BY expires_at " +
                "  LIMIT ?" +
                ")",
                cutoff, BATCH_SIZE
            )
        );
        totalDeleted += deleted;
        if (deleted < BATCH_SIZE) break;    // drained
        try { Thread.sleep(PAUSE_MS); } catch (InterruptedException e) { Thread.currentThread().interrupt(); break; }
    }
    log.info("reaped {} sessions in batches of {}", totalDeleted, BATCH_SIZE);
}
```

```yaml
# application.yml — isolate scheduler from checkout pool
datasource:
  checkout:
    maximum-pool-size: 20
  scheduler:
    maximum-pool-size: 2          # reaper cannot starve checkout
    connection-timeout: 30000
```

Each batch txn: ~10-50ms vs 4s. Locks held briefly, checkout path never queues past pool timeout. Separate pool = belt-and-suspenders so scheduler never competes for checkout's 20 connections.
